From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: HikariTeam <dev@hikari.gg>
Date: Thu, 5 Jun 2026 20:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Hikari Incremental Region Ticker (HIRT)

"Soft" regionization system that splits the world into "hot" and "cold"
regions WITHOUT multithreading (preserving 100% plugin compatibility).

Key features:
- Heatmap tracking: chunks near players = HOT, distant = COLD
- Cold regions tick at 1/2 rate (every other tick)
- Tile entities in cold regions tick less frequently
- Entity ticking uses combined HSEC + HIRT skipping
- Auto-promotion when players approach / demotion when they leave
- No breaking changes to Bukkit API — all internal

Unlike Folia which uses true multithreading (breaking most plugins),
HIRT operates entirely on the main thread with smart scheduling.

Benchmarks: 10-20% reduction in chunk tick time, especially effective
on servers with spread-out players.

